name: app.R
content:
#
# This is a Shiny web application. You can run the application by clicking
# the 'Run App' button above.
#
# Find out more about building applications with Shiny here:
#
#    https://shiny.posit.co/
#

library(shiny)
library(ggplot2)
library(plotly)
load("data/FB_demo_pop.RData")

# Define UI
ui <- fluidPage(
  titlePanel("Interactive Barplot with Data Selection"),
  
  # Dropdown to Select Sex
  selectInput("selected_region", "VÃ¤lj Kommun:", choices = unique(FB_population_tots_sex$region)),
  
  # Display Barplot
  plotlyOutput("barplot")
)

# Define Server
server <- function(input, output, session) {
  
  # Reactive Filtered Data
  filtered_data <- reactive({
    FB_population_tots_sex %>% filter(region == input$selected_region)
  })
  
  # Generate Barplot
  output$barplot <- renderPlotly({
    p <- ggplot(filtered_data(), aes(x=age, y=X2023, fill=sex)) +
      geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
      theme_minimal()
    
    ggplotly(p)
  })
}

# Run the application 
shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)
